'''Duilin''' can refer to:

* [[Duilin (son of Duinhir)]], a [[Gondorians|Gondorian]] soldier who lived during the [[War of the Ring]] and died in the [[Battle of the Pelennor Fields]].
* [[Duilin (elf of Gondolin)]], a lord who led the [[House of the Swallow]] in the [[The Book of Lost Tales|Lost Tale]] of "[[The Fall of Gondolin (chapter)|The Fall of Gondolin]]".
* [[Duilin (father of Saelon)|Duilin]], the father of [[Saelon]], a character from the ''[[The New Shadow]]''.
* The [[Nightingales|nightingale]], or "dusk-singer", which is ''duilinn'' in [[Sindarin]].
